result.name: Birdie

reviews.text:
Not recommend. 

Chicken thigh was the best among their menu but I had way better one elsewhere before. Worst chicken skin ever. Tiny portions. Worst of all - poor customer service. There are plenty of choices available in Hong Kong with the price they are charging.

I was utterly disappointed by the terrible service and staff who couldn't care less about their customers. Refused to listen to their customers, walked away while we were talking, came back and put down the bill. Appalling. The food is not outstanding either. I am a huge fan of yakitori and there are tons of places I would choose over Birdie.
Very tasty. Open BBQ kitchen. The liver is worth a try.
The Best Yakitori in town! Although is pricy place.

The food is is generally well cooked and of a high quality. However, do note that you will be essentially shelling out 35-45 HKD for one minuscule skewer of meat.

I hate to compare restaurants but at this price point, I might as well go to Yardbird where you will find slightly higher pricing in exchange for skewers that are significantly more substantial in portion and better tasting than Birdie's. 

What I'm trying to say is that both me and my old lady left Birdie hungry despite spending upwards of HKD 500 for our meal. 

The food at Birdie may be delicious but its ridiculously small portions and its awful bang for buck means that it will remain a hard pass for me.
